1
00:00:35,759 --> 00:00:36,560
Old Lu.

2
00:00:37,880 --> 00:00:38,600
You okay?

3
00:00:38,600 --> 00:00:40,359
No, my butt hurts.

4
00:00:40,759 --> 00:00:41,719
Something jabbed me.

5
00:00:43,159 --> 00:00:45,079
So this is that "studio apartment" you mentioned?

6
00:00:45,399 --> 00:00:46,600
Cut the nonsense.

7
00:00:46,799 --> 00:00:48,079
Just pull me up already.

8
00:00:51,359 --> 00:00:54,000
Why are there so many bones in this cave too?

9
00:00:58,200 --> 00:00:59,079
Look at these bones.

10
00:00:59,600 --> 00:01:01,119
Looks like they were just gnawed on.

11
00:01:03,000 --> 00:01:04,760
This... isn't a wolf den, is it?

12
00:01:10,400 --> 00:01:11,920
It's just a wolf cub.

13
00:01:12,239 --> 00:01:13,319
Is this really necessary?

14
00:01:13,439 --> 00:01:14,239
There's another one.

15
00:01:17,760 --> 00:01:18,840
Such a tiny little life.

16
00:01:18,840 --> 00:01:20,640
It didn't do anything to you.

17
00:01:20,640 --> 00:01:22,079
Why insist on killing it?

18
00:01:22,079 --> 00:01:22,799
Uncle Min.

19
00:01:23,439 --> 00:01:24,480
Keep your men in line.

20
00:01:25,120 --> 00:01:26,079
We're here for archaeology,

21
00:01:26,079 --> 00:01:27,159
not hunting.

22
00:01:27,200 --> 00:01:29,000
Wolf cubs grow up to eat people too.

23
00:01:29,359 --> 00:01:31,120
We're in the middle of nowhere anyway.

24
00:01:31,200 --> 00:01:31,640
You...

25
00:01:31,640 --> 00:01:32,760
"You" what?

26
00:01:32,760 --> 00:01:33,760
Shut your mouth.

27
00:01:33,760 --> 00:01:35,280
Come on, let's go, let's go.

28
00:01:35,599 --> 00:01:37,439
What kind of mess is this?

29
00:01:39,439 --> 00:01:40,239
Look at this.

30
00:01:41,680 --> 00:01:42,480
What is this?

31
00:01:56,200 --> 00:01:57,319
An eyeball pattern.

32
00:01:57,319 --> 00:01:58,120
There's more here.

33
00:01:58,400 --> 00:01:59,200
You see it?

34
00:02:01,200 --> 00:02:01,920
Commander Chen.

35
00:02:02,280 --> 00:02:03,359
The style of these murals

36
00:02:03,400 --> 00:02:05,319
is similar to the ones in Rahu Hall.

37
00:02:06,640 --> 00:02:09,960
Is this depicting some kind of ritual?

38
00:02:10,840 --> 00:02:13,000
Seems this was where the Jueda people

39
00:02:13,000 --> 00:02:14,719
once held some kind of ritual.

40
00:02:15,159 --> 00:02:16,319
After the ritual was finished,

41
00:02:16,879 --> 00:02:18,120
they would take some

42
00:02:18,159 --> 00:02:19,800
symbolic stone statues

43
00:02:20,080 --> 00:02:21,400
and transport them into the snowy mountains.

44
00:02:21,400 --> 00:02:23,919
Isn't that basically a sacred sealing rite?

45
00:02:24,879 --> 00:02:25,599
Look here.

46
00:02:25,919 --> 00:02:26,840
There's a pagoda here too.

47
00:02:27,560 --> 00:02:30,439
Who would build a pagoda in the snowy mountains?

48
00:02:32,240 --> 00:02:33,039
One level,

49
00:02:33,759 --> 00:02:34,560
two levels,

50
00:02:34,800 --> 00:02:35,599
three levels,

51
00:02:35,879 --> 00:02:36,680
four levels,

52
00:02:37,039 --> 00:02:37,919
five levels,

53
00:02:38,560 --> 00:02:39,439
six levels,

54
00:02:40,080 --> 00:02:40,960
seven levels,

55
00:02:41,319 --> 00:02:42,159
eight levels,

56
00:02:43,639 --> 00:02:44,719
nine levels.

57
00:02:46,240 --> 00:02:47,199
The Nine-Tiered Pagoda.

58
00:03:00,759 --> 00:03:01,960
Are the wolves coming?

59
00:03:02,000 --> 00:03:03,919
We need to leave before the wolves return.

60
00:03:05,639 --> 00:03:06,800
Don't go scaring yourselves.

61
00:03:06,879 --> 00:03:08,120
Even if the wolves do come back,

62
00:03:08,120 --> 00:03:09,199
they won't be that fast, right?

63
00:03:15,120 --> 00:03:16,000
Brother Chen.

64
00:03:18,719 --> 00:03:19,560
Enough talk.

65
00:03:19,680 --> 00:03:20,400
Let's get out of here, fast.

66
00:03:20,400 --> 00:03:20,560
Alright.

67
00:03:20,560 --> 00:03:21,919
You lead the way, I'll cover the rear.

68
00:03:25,680 --> 00:03:26,280
Remember,

69
00:03:26,639 --> 00:03:28,479
do not shoot unless the wolves attack us.

70
00:03:28,800 --> 00:03:29,599
Got it?

71
00:03:32,000 --> 00:03:32,680
Let's go!

72
00:03:32,800 --> 00:03:33,319
Move!

73
00:03:45,120 --> 00:03:45,960
They're really here.

74
00:03:50,080 --> 00:03:52,360
We're done for. We're surrounded.

75
00:03:52,479 --> 00:03:54,560
Everyone, get your weapons out, quick!

76
00:03:56,680 --> 00:03:57,080
Fatty!

77
00:03:57,439 --> 00:03:57,840
Hurry!

78
00:03:58,840 --> 00:03:59,400
Remember,

79
00:04:00,360 --> 00:04:01,680
only wound them, don't kill the wolves.

80
00:04:02,759 --> 00:04:03,840
Old Chen, here.

81
00:04:03,919 --> 00:04:05,599
These wolves come in packs.

82
00:04:05,599 --> 00:04:06,360
These few arrows...

83
00:04:06,360 --> 00:04:08,080
These few arrows won't even scratch them.

84
00:04:08,159 --> 00:04:09,919
If worse comes to worst, use the homemade explosives.

85
00:04:09,919 --> 00:04:11,280
Once the pack closes in, we shoot.

86
00:04:11,360 --> 00:04:12,439
They'll fall back temporarily.

87
00:04:12,719 --> 00:04:13,319
At that moment,

88
00:04:13,400 --> 00:04:14,719
throw the explosives behind you.

89
00:04:14,840 --> 00:04:15,520
Okay, okay, okay.

90
00:04:18,800 --> 00:04:19,519
Hurry up!

91
00:04:20,480 --> 00:04:21,959
You're killing me here!

92
00:04:23,160 --> 00:04:24,000
Hurry up, Old Lian!

93
00:04:27,480 --> 00:04:28,680
As long as the wind doesn't pick up,

94
00:04:28,800 --> 00:04:31,000
we'll get through tonight.

95
00:04:32,759 --> 00:04:33,639
The wind's coming!

96
00:04:33,759 --> 00:04:34,720
Wolf packs have one trait:

97
00:04:35,040 --> 00:04:36,560
they all follow the alpha's command.

98
00:04:37,120 --> 00:04:37,800
The alpha wolf.

99
00:04:37,879 --> 00:04:38,879
But how do we know

100
00:04:38,879 --> 00:04:40,279
which one's the alpha?

101
00:04:40,759 --> 00:04:42,560
The alpha usually stays at the back of the pack.

102
00:04:48,319 --> 00:04:49,000
Take that!

103
00:04:55,160 --> 00:04:56,160
Wolf pack brothers!

104
00:04:56,480 --> 00:04:58,279
Right, like father and son in battle.

105
00:05:13,959 --> 00:05:15,680
Wolf packs operate with strict order.

106
00:05:15,680 --> 00:05:16,920
The alpha must be in a spot

107
00:05:16,920 --> 00:05:18,240
where it can survey everything.

108
00:05:18,800 --> 00:05:20,399
That should be this hilltop.

109
00:05:21,759 --> 00:05:24,439
Look, that should be the alpha.

110
00:05:27,839 --> 00:05:30,120
Why are the wolves moving forward again?

111
00:05:30,120 --> 00:05:32,480
Weren't they supposed to be afraid of fire?

112
00:05:32,560 --> 00:05:33,319
The alpha must have just

113
00:05:33,319 --> 00:05:34,360
issued another attack command.

114
00:05:34,360 --> 00:05:35,639
It's gotta be Old Chen.

115
00:05:35,639 --> 00:05:38,000
His negotiations with the alpha broke down.

116
00:05:57,120 --> 00:05:57,800
Careful!

117
00:06:02,399 --> 00:06:03,360
Stop, stop blowing!

118
00:06:05,839 --> 00:06:08,199
We're done for. The fire's out.

119
00:06:09,279 --> 00:06:10,879
It's out, it's out!

120
00:06:12,920 --> 00:06:13,600
Fatty!

121
00:06:13,680 --> 00:06:14,399
Give me the rope!

122
00:06:14,399 --> 00:06:15,120
Catch!

123
00:06:19,519 --> 00:06:20,199
Fatty!

124
00:06:22,439 --> 00:06:23,120
Fatty!

125
00:06:29,600 --> 00:06:30,160
You...

126
00:06:32,240 --> 00:06:32,800
You...

127
00:06:36,199 --> 00:06:36,759
You...

128
00:07:10,680 --> 00:07:11,000
No, no, no.

129
00:07:11,000 --> 00:07:12,160
I, I, I...

130
00:07:12,759 --> 00:07:13,560
It's me.

131
00:07:14,879 --> 00:07:16,319
Brother Xiao Qi.

132
00:07:16,319 --> 00:07:18,480
What... what happened?

133
00:07:18,639 --> 00:07:19,680
They... they retreated.

134
00:07:21,439 --> 00:07:23,240
The wolves just ran off like that.

135
00:07:24,040 --> 00:07:25,439
Old Chen and the others succeeded.

136
00:07:33,079 --> 00:07:34,279
It's the final step.

137
00:07:34,480 --> 00:07:36,079
It all comes down to this.

138
00:07:37,000 --> 00:07:37,959
Are you nervous?

139
00:07:38,920 --> 00:07:40,240
I'm about to wet myself.

140
00:07:41,360 --> 00:07:42,199
I am a little, too.

141
00:07:43,839 --> 00:07:44,879
It's all up to you.

142
00:07:46,399 --> 00:07:47,319
Leave it to me.

143
00:07:48,279 --> 00:07:48,879
One.

144
00:07:49,199 --> 00:07:49,800
Two.

145
00:07:50,480 --> 00:07:51,240
Three.

146
00:07:52,160 --> 00:07:53,000
Officer He!

147
00:07:53,519 --> 00:07:55,720
Come quick! Old Chen fought the alpha

148
00:07:55,720 --> 00:07:57,319
and fell from up there!

149
00:07:57,480 --> 00:07:58,199
What?

150
00:07:58,759 --> 00:07:59,720
Hurry up!

151
00:08:00,560 --> 00:08:01,800
What happened? Go check on him, quick!

152
00:08:03,160 --> 00:08:04,639
Chen Youxi, are you okay?

153
00:08:05,399 --> 00:08:06,120
Old Chen!

154
00:08:06,600 --> 00:08:07,759
Old Chen, I'm coming!

155
00:08:07,759 --> 00:08:08,240
What's wrong?

156
00:08:08,240 --> 00:08:08,959
I, I, I...

157
00:08:08,959 --> 00:08:09,720
Enough.

158
00:08:10,319 --> 00:08:11,959
The wolves are gone already.

159
00:08:11,959 --> 00:08:13,639
Can't you give those two some space?

160
00:08:13,639 --> 00:08:14,680
Stop butting in.

161
00:08:14,839 --> 00:08:15,839
You're so bad.

162
00:08:16,879 --> 00:08:18,560
Where are you hurt? Let me see.

163
00:08:19,279 --> 00:08:20,199
Is it serious?

164
00:08:20,279 --> 00:08:21,079
My ribs...

165
00:08:21,240 --> 00:08:22,199
Listen to me.

166
00:08:23,879 --> 00:08:24,639
I might...

167
00:08:25,600 --> 00:08:26,879
not make it through tonight.

168
00:08:26,879 --> 00:08:28,079
What nonsense are you talking?

169
00:08:28,079 --> 00:08:28,920
Listen to me.

170
00:08:29,879 --> 00:08:31,360
I have only one wish.

171
00:08:33,559 --> 00:08:34,240
Could you...

172
00:08:35,480 --> 00:08:36,279
give me a kiss?

173
00:08:41,559 --> 00:08:42,480
You're tricking me, aren't you?

174
00:08:48,320 --> 00:08:49,320
What are you all staring at?

175
00:08:49,480 --> 00:08:50,159
What are you looking at?

176
00:08:50,639 --> 00:08:53,240
Well... uh... we'll get going first.

177
00:08:53,279 --> 00:08:55,039
Yeah, take good care of Old Chen's wounds.

178
00:08:55,039 --> 00:08:56,240
We'll wait for you up ahead.

179
00:08:56,440 --> 00:08:57,639
What's the big idea?

180
00:08:57,639 --> 00:08:59,200
At a time like this?

181
00:09:01,159 --> 00:09:02,720
So this last wish of mine,

182
00:09:03,440 --> 00:09:04,720
can it be granted?

183
00:09:17,639 --> 00:09:19,759
Commander Chen, we finally got out.

184
00:09:20,919 --> 00:09:22,320
On our way to Xiaduo Yuzhang,

185
00:09:22,320 --> 00:09:23,519
is there any hidden spot

186
00:09:23,519 --> 00:09:24,600
where we can set up camp?

187
00:09:24,639 --> 00:09:25,639
Once we enter Shenluo Gorge,

188
00:09:25,799 --> 00:09:27,480
we're basically inside Xiaduo Yuzhang.

189
00:09:28,080 --> 00:09:29,679
We'll rest in that grove of trees,

190
00:09:30,159 --> 00:09:31,639
then head toward Shenluo Gorge.

191
00:09:32,559 --> 00:09:34,840
Brother Xiao Qi, didn't you say before

192
00:09:34,840 --> 00:09:37,159
we were going to Xiaduo Yuzhang?

193
00:09:37,360 --> 00:09:39,399
Where did this Shenluo Gorge come from?

194
00:09:39,840 --> 00:09:41,840
After I entered that cave earlier,

195
00:09:42,159 --> 00:09:44,679
the murals on the walls showed me the way.

196
00:09:44,679 --> 00:09:46,159
The murals clearly depict

197
00:09:46,799 --> 00:09:47,679
the Nine-Tiered Pagoda located

198
00:09:47,679 --> 00:09:49,200
among four surrounding snow mountains.

199
00:09:49,639 --> 00:09:50,759
In the Xiaduo Yuzhang range,

200
00:09:51,159 --> 00:09:52,320
I've only seen one place

201
00:09:52,679 --> 00:09:54,120
surrounded by four snow peaks,

202
00:09:54,320 --> 00:09:55,480
just like in the mural.

203
00:09:56,000 --> 00:09:56,840
Shenluo Gorge.

204
00:09:58,840 --> 00:09:59,759
Keep up at the back!

205
00:10:42,080 --> 00:10:43,440
That right there is Shenluo Gorge.

206
00:10:45,320 --> 00:10:46,240
Once inside Shenluo Gorge,

207
00:10:47,000 --> 00:10:48,759
we'll reach the snow peaks from the mural.

208
00:10:49,759 --> 00:10:50,919
We need to lighten our gear.

209
00:10:52,039 --> 00:10:54,679
The mule team won't be able to keep up.

210
00:11:04,759 --> 00:11:06,120
We have to go down from here.

211
00:11:07,840 --> 00:11:08,759
This looks fun!

212
00:11:09,039 --> 00:11:10,399
Just like a giant slide.

213
00:11:11,440 --> 00:11:13,799
Easy to slide down this ice, hard to climb back up.

214
00:11:14,279 --> 00:11:16,039
So we need to find an anchor point

215
00:11:16,320 --> 00:11:17,440
and leave the rope here.

216
00:11:17,840 --> 00:11:19,159
That way, when we come back,

217
00:11:19,240 --> 00:11:20,559
we can use it to climb back up.

218
00:11:24,279 --> 00:11:25,080
Be careful!

219
00:11:28,600 --> 00:11:29,720
When everyone goes down,

220
00:11:30,200 --> 00:11:31,559
copy Duji's movements.

221
00:11:35,679 --> 00:11:36,360
Slow down.

222
00:12:10,759 --> 00:12:11,320
Commander Chen!

223
00:12:13,240 --> 00:12:13,799
Look!

224
00:12:18,039 --> 00:12:18,720
Hey, buddy.

225
00:12:18,840 --> 00:12:19,720
Move aside, would you?

226
00:12:21,720 --> 00:12:22,799
Step aside, pal.

227
00:12:22,799 --> 00:12:23,960
Take a hint, will you?

228
00:12:27,279 --> 00:12:28,080
Just keep moving.

229
00:12:28,559 --> 00:12:30,240
What a waste of a brain.

230
00:12:35,120 --> 00:12:35,759
Fatty!

231
00:12:37,279 --> 00:12:37,960
Fatty!

232
00:12:39,559 --> 00:12:40,240
Fat...

233
00:12:44,039 --> 00:12:44,840
Fatty!

234
00:12:50,519 --> 00:12:51,320
Grab on!

235
00:12:55,600 --> 00:12:58,200
Why weren't you more careful?

236
00:13:17,120 --> 00:13:18,200
You stupid woman!

237
00:13:18,279 --> 00:13:19,480
Did you just trip me?

238
00:13:19,720 --> 00:13:20,600
Stop talking nonsense!

239
00:13:20,679 --> 00:13:22,440
White-hair, mind your own business.

240
00:13:22,639 --> 00:13:23,440
Let me tell you.

241
00:13:23,480 --> 00:13:24,519
If it wasn't her, it was you.

242
00:13:24,519 --> 00:13:25,360
You shameless pair!

243
00:13:25,360 --> 00:13:26,279
Neither of you is any good.

244
00:13:27,000 --> 00:13:29,600
I'm saying, with your weight,

245
00:13:29,600 --> 00:13:31,399
altitude sickness comes easily.

246
00:13:31,759 --> 00:13:33,960
Who knows if you just lost your footing

247
00:13:34,000 --> 00:13:35,000
and lost face

248
00:13:35,240 --> 00:13:36,759
and now you're blaming us.

249
00:13:37,720 --> 00:13:38,159
No.

250
00:13:38,159 --> 00:13:39,879
What's that got to do with my weight?

251
00:13:39,879 --> 00:13:40,919
You're twisting the facts.

252
00:13:40,919 --> 00:13:41,720
All right, all right.

253
00:13:42,120 --> 00:13:43,559
This is no place for arguing.

254
00:13:43,759 --> 00:13:44,720
If an avalanche hits,

255
00:13:44,720 --> 00:13:45,919
we'll all die here.

256
00:13:46,039 --> 00:13:46,759
Let's move.

257
00:14:02,360 --> 00:14:04,159
These four snow-capped peaks

258
00:14:04,679 --> 00:14:06,759
look exactly the same.

259
00:14:07,440 --> 00:14:08,639
How can we tell them apart?

260
00:14:08,639 --> 00:14:10,879
Where's the Nine-Tiered Pagoda?

261
00:14:10,960 --> 00:14:12,679
The place we're standing now

262
00:14:13,440 --> 00:14:15,000
is right where these four snow peaks'

263
00:14:15,480 --> 00:14:17,639
glaciers converge.

264
00:14:18,519 --> 00:14:20,320
The terrain is rough and uneven,

265
00:14:21,200 --> 00:14:23,200
crisscrossed with ice trenches and crevasses.

266
00:14:24,159 --> 00:14:25,759
So when this pagoda was built,

267
00:14:26,200 --> 00:14:27,480
the Jueda people

268
00:14:27,840 --> 00:14:30,120
hadn't yet developed a mature construction system.

269
00:14:30,480 --> 00:14:31,840
Look at these four snow mountains.

270
00:14:32,399 --> 00:14:34,279
Don't they seem to be guarding

271
00:14:35,039 --> 00:14:37,000
or paying homage to the Nine-Tiered Pagoda?

272
00:14:37,919 --> 00:14:39,120
So if you ask me,

273
00:14:39,600 --> 00:14:40,840
once we find

274
00:14:40,960 --> 00:14:42,639
the cave with the stone statue,

275
00:14:42,919 --> 00:14:45,000
we should get a clue to the exact

276
00:14:45,440 --> 00:14:46,879
location of the Nine-Tiered Pagoda.

277
00:14:47,200 --> 00:14:47,960
Look here.

278
00:14:48,480 --> 00:14:49,840
Surrounded by four snow mountains.

279
00:14:50,720 --> 00:14:51,519
So this stone statue

280
00:14:51,519 --> 00:14:53,440
must be beneath these glaciers.

281
00:14:53,799 --> 00:14:55,200
Everyone knows it's down there.

282
00:14:55,960 --> 00:14:57,039
But where do we look?

283
00:15:00,200 --> 00:15:00,879
Old Lu.

284
00:15:01,559 --> 00:15:02,360
Come, come, come.

285
00:15:04,519 --> 00:15:05,879
Look beneath that glacier.

286
00:15:10,559 --> 00:15:11,480
Brother Chen,

287
00:15:12,159 --> 00:15:13,679
Did you find something?

288
00:15:15,200 --> 00:15:16,440
What is it?

